As part of his continued efforts to cushion the effects of the coronavirus pandemic resulting from the lockdown in the nation, Abuja-based real estate company, T Pumpy, on Wednesday distributed food items to residents of Abuja, FCT. The gesture came at a time Muslim faithful are celebrating this year’s Eid-El-Kabir. Speaking while distributing the items, which included bags of rice, rams in his office on Wednesday, the MD/CEO, Akintayo Adaralegbe, said he is not unaware of the fact that the coronavirus pandemic has been eating deep into people pocket, thereby making it difficult for some families to feed.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-822945" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.24-PM-1.jpeg" alt="" width="713" height="713" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.24-PM-1.jpeg 713w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.24-PM-1-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.24-PM-1-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.24-PM-1-80x80.jpeg 80w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.24-PM-1-45x45.jpeg 45w" sizes="(max-width: 713px) 100vw, 713px"> He said the gesture was done the company to cushion the effects of the current situation. He noted that this is not the first time the company would be reaching out to people during this period. Mr. Adaralegbe added that the company would continue to reach out to the less privileged in the society.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-822944" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.23-PM.jpeg" alt="" width="1080" height="720" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.23-PM.jpeg 1080w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.23-PM-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.23-PM-1024x683.jpeg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px"> Meanwhile, T. Pumpy Concept Limited is set to reward architects, realtors and lawyers.
According to the MD/CEO, Mr. Adaralegebe, this package will be beneficial to all classes of income/salary earners.
He explains below. “Meanwhile, we want to bring on board three categories of professionals to work with on this.
“They include, professional architects, barristers and realtors. “For architects:- 20 entries will be taken, to come up with different structural designs (building prototypes will be explained to you). You will get a token of 50k each for attendance.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-822943" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-26-at-7.43.03-PM.jpeg" alt="" width="360" height="360" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-26-at-7.43.03-PM.jpeg 360w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-26-at-7.43.03-PM-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-26-at-7.43.03-PM-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-26-at-7.43.03-PM-80x80.jpeg 80w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-26-at-7.43.03-PM-45x45.jpeg 45w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px"> “Benefit:- the architect with the best design will get a reward of 1m ( one million naira only).
“However, for those in the legal profession,:- 20 entries will be taken, to come up with drafting detailed agreement, business transaction, MOU etc. You will get a token of 50k each for attendance. “Benefit:- the barrister to come up with the best terms gets 1m (one million naira only).”
“Realtors:- 20 entries will also be considered, you will be given full details of our offer packages. You will get a token of 20k each for attendance.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-822941" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.25-PM.jpeg" alt="" width="360" height="360" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.25-PM.jpeg 360w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.25-PM-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.25-PM-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.25-PM-80x80.jpeg 80w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-30-at-6.50.25-PM-45x45.jpeg 45w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px"> “Benefit:- the realtor with the highest referral (commitment-wise) at the end of the offer gets a brand new 2015/2016 Toyota Corolla. “To qualify, architects:- must be registered, with not less than 7yrs practice experience. “ Barristers:- 7 years post call-to-bar. realtors:- must be a registered member of NIESV/ESVARBON with CAC registration of not less than 7 years. “To apply: forward application/cover letter to tpumpyconcept1@gmail.com. Deadline for submission of application:- August 3rd, 2020. All qualified candidates will be contacted.”<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-822940" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-26-at-7.43.02-PM.jpeg" alt="" width="1008" height="756" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-26-at-7.43.02-PM.jpeg 1008w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/WhatsApp-Image-2020-07-26-at-7.43.02-PM-300x225.jpeg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1008px) 100vw, 1008px">